cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper focuses on machine lipreading, which involves visually interpreting the movement of face regions. This falls under the domain of computer vision. 
2. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with automatic speech recognition (ASR) which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). 
3. cs.SD (Sound): Although the paper focuses on visual interpretation of speech, it still deals with speech recognition and transcription, which is related to sound processing. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an end-to-end deep neural network based lipreading system, which is a machine learning approach. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with lipreading from video frames, which is a multimedia application.
